main event: An unidentified object was sighted, described as leaving an irregular luminous vapor trail at a high altitude.
interesting points: The object was first observed at 10,000 feet and later at 100,000 feet., The estimated speed of the object was 500 knots., The sighting occurred on 27/0732Z September 1964., The object was bearing 205 degrees true., Weather conditions at the time were clear with a sea state of 2.
sighted object: one unidentified object leaving a vapor trail
